import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='Miles_per_Gallon', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['Miles_per_Gallon'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(data['Miles_per_Gallon'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Miles_per_Gallon?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='Weight_in_lbs', color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['Weight_in_lbs'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['Weight_in_lbs'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['Weight_in_lbs'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['Weight_in_lbs'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Weight_in_lbs?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Year'])]
    data['Year'] = data['Year'].dt.year
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='Year', y='Miles_per_Gallon', data=data)
    chart.axhline(y=data['Miles_per_Gallon'].median(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Median')
    chart.legend()
    plt.title('How has the Miles_per_Gallon changed over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
